title="Principles of Mathematical Analysis">Principles of Mathematical Analysis</fr:link>, Appendix to Ch. 1</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Dedekind Cut</html:dfn> is a subset <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha \subset \mathbb {Q}]]></fr:tex> such that:
<fr:ol><fr:li><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha ]]></fr:tex> is not empty and also <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha \neq \mathbb {Q}]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>If <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p\in \alpha ]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[q\in \mathbb {Q}]]></fr:tex> with <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[q<p]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[q\in \alpha ]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>If <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p\in \alpha ]]></fr:tex>, then there exists some <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[r\in \alpha ]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[r\in \alpha ]]></fr:tex></fr:li></fr:ol></fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
